%section#pricing
  .container
    %h2
      Pricing
    %p
      Our aim is to charge a fair and transparent success when our members find a new client through Uplink.
    #pricing-badge
      .percentage
        10%
      .max
        max. 12 months
        %br
        max. 1,500€ per client total
    %p
      We ask the freelancer to pay a fee of 10% of their monthly earnings, for max. 12 months, capped at
      %strong
        1,500€ per client in total (not monthly).
      This means that if a freelancer finds a client and works with them for a long time and over many projects, he will not have to pay any more fees once the cap is reached. Most of our members simply add the fee to their hourly rate, so in the end they don't even notice it.

= partial 'partials/section-about'

%section#apply.gray-bg
  .container
    %h2
      Apply to join Uplink
    %p
      If you are a senior developer
      %strong
        based in Berlin, Germany,
      with at least a couple of years experience in freelancing, please apply below!
    = form_tag config[:form_url] do
      = hidden_field_tag '_subject', value: 'Freelancer application'
      .row
        .col-sm-5.col-md-4.col-md-offset-1
          .form-group
            = text_field_tag 'name', class: 'form-control', required: true, placeholder: 'Your name'
          .form-group
            = email_field_tag 'email', class: 'form-control', required: true, placeholder: 'Your email'
          .form-group
            = text_field_tag 'location', class: 'form-control', required: true, placeholder: 'Your location'
        .col-sm-7.col-md-6
          .form-group
            %textarea#message.form-control.white-large{ name: 'message', required: true, placeholder: "Tell us a bit about yourself! Are you a frontend, backend, fullstack or mobile developer? What programming languages and frameworks do you like to work with? Do you enjoy working for small startups, agencies, or big companies? Remote or on-site? Please include links to your profiles on GitHub, Linkedin, and any other service you deem relevant!" }
          = submit_tag 'Submit', class: 'btn btn-primary', data: { loading: 'Please wait...' }
    = partial 'partials/form-messages'

